name: AtafonaCollection#01
description: Made by Fernando Luiz, an Brazilian artist who is minimalist par excellence, Fernando Luiz is, above all, an interpreter. The line of the drawing, always highlighted, reveals its graphic vocation. The mark of his trajectory is a transparent diversity, which unmasks the non-conformity and the nature of an experimenter, resulting in a type of plural dialect. His favorite themes are cultures and religious archetypes, tribal graphics and forms of Nature.
